PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F434A1776777069
OL,3,CWhat is stalking and who can help you?
OL,4,CHow to recognise the signs
OL,6,FAside from personal characteristics
OL,7,Fsuch as gender and age, someone's
OL,8,Fprofession could increase their
OL,9,Fchances of falling victim to stalking.
OL,10,FResearch has found those working in an
OL,11,Fempathetic role - such as
OL,12,Fhairdressing, a therapist, or a
OL,13,Fmasseuse - may find themselves at an
OL,14,Felevated risk.
OL,16,FSome stalkers are motivated by
OL,17,Fresentment and therefore anyone who
OL,18,Fhas to deliver bad news could also be
OL,19,Fat an increased risk.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G9/17
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
